CatDescriptText: Related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1962, pg. 14A, reads: "The D.I.s and Terri - The fabulous group of club women whose benefit for MENDS, last Sunday, was a terrific success, entertained at dinner Saturday night for Terri Springer (far left), their star model. Snapped in Terri's suite at the Penn-Sheraton are members, far left, standing: Margaret Watson, president; seated: Hilda Logan, new member; Bernice Coleman and Mary Jean Eaton, associate members; charter members Juanita Drake and Gloria Grate, on floor; on couch, left to right: Evelyn Christian, new member; Birdie Dunlap, associate member, and Nellye Barron, charter member, who was chairman of the affair."
TitMainTitle: Terri Springer wearing dark dress and three strand necklace, seated on sofa holding document, surrounded by nine members of the D. I. Club, clockwise from right: Margaret Watson, Bernice Coleman, Nellye Barron, Gloria Golden Grate, Juanita Drake, Hilda Logan, Mary Jean Eaton, Evelyn Christian, and Birdie Dunlap, gathered in suite of Penn Sheraton Hotel
